name: src/Loc.js
Pos
description: Represents a single location in the source string.

name: next
description: Advance the pos by any character.

name: onNextLine
description: Poc after a newline.

name: onNextColumn
description: Loc after a non-newline character.

name: onPrevColumn
description:
Undoes {@link onNextLine}.
Only call this is you know this is not the first column.

name: Loc
description: Range of text in the source string.

name: end
description: Beginning of text.

name: singleCharLoc
description: Loc consisting of the character at `pos`.

name: StartLine
description: First line number for a source string; they start at 1.

name: StartColumn
description: Fist column number for a line; they start at 0.

name: StartPos
description: First {@link Pos} in a source string.

name: src/ast.js
Node
description: Base type of all ASTs.

name: toJSON
description: Convert to JSON.

name: type
description:
For compatibility with other AST representations,
all Node instances have a 'type' property that is the name of that type.

name: Declaration
description: Line that declares new locals.

name: Statement
description: Blocks of code have lines that are Statements or Declarations.

name: Expression
description:
Code that has a value.
To use one in a statement position, see ExpressionStatement.

name: Pattern
description: Can go in a parameter list or on the left side of an assignment.

name: Identifier
description:
A JavaScript identifier.
It is assumed that you have called `mangleIdentifier` as appropriate.
See also {@link identifier}.

name: VariableDeclarator
description: Single declaration within a {@link VariableDeclaration}.

name: VariableDeclarationKind
description: Accepted kinds of {@link VariableDeclaration}.

name: VariableDeclaration
description:
Declares and optionally initializes many variables.
Must be at least one declaration.

name: EmptyStatement
description:
An empty statement, i.e., a solitary semicolon.
Not useful for code generation, but some parsers will return these.

name: BlockStatement
description: A block statement, i.e., a sequence of statements surrounded by braces.

name: ExpressionStatement
description:
An expression statement, i.e., a statement consisting of a single expression.
See `esast.util toStatement toStatements`.

name: IfStatement
description: An if (or if ... else) statement.

name: LabeledStatement
description: A statement prefixed by a label.

name: constructor
description: The `break` keyword.

name: ContinueStatement
description: The `continue` keyword.

name: SwitchStatement
description:
`switch (discriminant) { cases }`
Only the last entry of `cases` is allowed to be `default`.

name: SwitchCase
description:
A single `case` within a SwitchStatement.
If `test` is `null`, this is the `default` case.

name: ReturnStatement
description: The `return` keyword, optionally followed by an Expression to return.

name: ThrowStatement
description:
The `throw` keyword, and something to throw.
See `esast.util throwError`.

name: TryStatement
description:
`try { block } catch (handler.param) { handler.body } finally { finalizer }`
At least one of `handler` or `finalizer` must be non-null.

name: CatchClause
description: Must be *part* of a {@link TryStatement} -- does *not* follow it.

name: WhileStatement
description: `while (test) body`

name: DoWhileStatement
description: `do body while (test)`

name: ForStatement
description:
`for (init; test; update) body`
Not to be confused with ForInStatement or ForOfStatement.

name: ForInStatement
description: `for (left in right) body`

name: ForOfStatement
description: `for (left of right) body`

name: DebuggerStatement
description: The `debugger` keyword.

name: FunctionAbstract
description: FunctionDeclaration | FunctionExpression | ArrowFunctionExpression

name: FunctionDeclaration
description: {@link Function} in declaration position.

name: ThisExpression
description: The `this` keyword.

name: ArrayExpression
description: `[ elements ]`

name: PropertyKind
description: Accepted kinds of {@link Property}.

name: Property
description: Part of an ObjectExpression.

name: ObjectExpression
description: An object literal.

name: FunctionExpression
description: {@link Function} in expression position.

name: ArrowFunctionExpression
description: Like FunctionExpression but uses the `params => body` form.

name: SequenceExpression
description:
`expressions[0], expressions[1], ...`
Expression composed of other expressions, separated by the comma operator.
Not* for parameter lists.

name: UnaryOperator
description: Accepted kinds of {@link UnaryExpression}.

name: UnaryExpression
description:
`operator argument`
Calls a unary operator.

name: prefix
description: Always true. Needed for comparibility with estree.

name: BinaryOperator
description: Accepted kinds of {@link BinaryExpression}.

name: BinaryExpression
description:
`left operator right`
Calls a binary operator.

name: AssignmentOperator
description: Accepted kinds of {@link AssignmentExpression}.

name: AssignmentExpression
description:
`left operator right`
Mutates an existing variable.
Do not confuse with VariableDeclaration.

name: UpdateOperator
description: Accepted kinds of {@link UpdateExpression}.

name: UpdateExpression
description:
`++argument` or `argument++`
Increments or decrements a number.

name: LogicalOperator
description: Accepted kinds of {@link LogicalExpression}.

name: LogicalExpression
description:
`left operator right`
Calls a lazy logical operator.

name: ConditionalExpression
description: `test ? consequent : alternate`

name: NewExpression
description:
`new callee(arguments)`
Just like {@link CallExpression} but with `new` in front.

name: CallExpression
description: `callee(arguments)`

name: SpreadElement
description: `...args` in a CallExpression.

name: MemberExpression
description:
If computed === true, `object[property]`.
Else, `object.property` -- meaning property should be an Identifier.

name: computed
description: Needed for compatibility with estree.

name: YieldExpression
description: `yield argument` or `yield* argument`

name: TemplateLiteral
description:
A template with no tag.
It alternates between quasis and expressions.
It should begin and end with quasis, using {@link TemplateElement.empty} if necessary.
This means that `${1}${2}` has 3 empty quasis!

name: TemplateElement
description: Part of a TemplateLiteral.

name: forRawString
description: TemplateElement whose raw source is `str`.

name: forString
description:
TemplateElement evaluating to `str`.
Uses escape sequences as necessary.

name: empty
description: TemplateElement with empty value.

name: tail
description: Use this to mark the last TemplateElement.

name: TaggedTemplateExpression
description: TemplateLiteral with a tag in front, like`this`.

name: ObjectPattern
description:
`{ a, b: c } =`
Object deconstructing pattern.

name: AssignmentProperty
description:
Just like a Property, but kind is always `init`.
Although technically its own type, `_.type` will be 'Property'.

name: ArrayPattern
description:
`[ a, b ] = ...`.
Array deconstructing pattern.

name: RestElement
description:
Can be the last argument to a FunctionExpression/FunctionDeclaration
or  go at the end of an ArrayPattern.

name: MethodDefinitionKind
description: Accepted kinds of {@link MethodDefinition}.

name: MethodDefinition
description: Part of a {@link ClassBody}.

name: ClassBody
description: Contents of a {@link Class}.

name: Class
description: {@link ClassDeclaration} | {@link ClassExpression}

name: ClassDeclaration
description: {@link Class} in declaration position.

name: ClassExpression
description: {@link Class} in expression position.

name: ModuleSpecifier
description: A specifier in an import or export declaration.

name: ImportSpecifierAbstract
description: {@link ImportSpecifier} | {@link ImportDefaultSpecifier} | {@link ImportNamespaceSpecifier}

name: ImportDeclaration
description:
`import specifiers from source`
Only one specifier may be a ImportDefaultSpecifier.
If there is an ImportNamespaceSpecifier, it must be the only specifier.

name: ImportSpecifier
description:
A non-default import. Used in an ImportDeclaration.
For `import { a } from "source"`, just pass one argument and local will = imported.
For `import { a as b } from "source"`, make imported `a` and local `b`.

name: ImportDefaultSpecifier
description: The default export, as in `import a from "source"`.

name: ImportNamespaceSpecifier
description: Object of every export, as in `import * as a from "source"`.

name: ExportSpecifier
description:
A non-default export. Used in an ExportNamedDeclaration.
For `export { a } from "source"`, just pass one argument local will = exported.
For `export { a as b }`, make exported `b` and local `a`.

name: ExportNamedDeclaration
description:
Exports multiple values as in `export { a, b as c }`.
If source !== null,
re-exports from that module as in `export { ... } from "source"`.

name: ExportDefaultDeclaration
description: `export default declaration`

name: ExportAllDeclaration
description: `export * from source`

name: src/mangle-identifier.js
content:
/**
Convert a name to a valid JavaScript identifier.
@param {String} name Can be any string.
@return {String}
*/
export default function mangleIdentifier(name) {
	return forbiddenNames.has(name) ?
		`_${name}` :
		name.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9$_]/g, _ => `_${_.charCodeAt(0)}`)
}

/** `false` iff `name` is a valid JavaScript identifier. */
export function needsMangle(name) {
	return forbiddenNames.has(name) || !propertyNameOk(name)
}

/** `true` iff `name` can be used as a property name using dot syntax (`a.b`). */
export function propertyNameOk(name) {
	return name.search(/[^a-zA-Z0-9$_]/) === -1
}

/** Undoes {@link mangleIdentifier}. */
export function unmangle(name) {
	if (name[0] === '_') {
		const rest = name.slice(1)
		if (forbiddenNames.has(rest))
			return rest
	}
	return name.replace(/_\d+/g, match => {
		const charCode = match.slice(1)
		const n = Number.parseInt(charCode)
		const ch = String.fromCharCode(n)
		return ch === '\0' ? match : ch
	})
}

/** Set of JavaScript keywords. */
export const forbiddenNames = new Set([
	'abstract',
	'arguments',
	'boolean',
	'break',
	'byte',
	'case',
	'catch',
	'char',
	'class',
	'comment',
	'const',
	'continue',
	'debugger',
	'default',
	'delete',
	'do',
	'double',
	'else',
	'enum',
	'eval',
	'export',
	'extends',
	'false',
	'final',
	'finally',
	'float',
	'for',
	'function',
	'function*',
	'goto',
	'if',
	'implements',
	'import',
	'in',
	'instanceOf',
	'int',
	'interface',
	'label',
	'long',
	'module',
	'native',
	'new',
	'null',
	'package',
	'private',
	'protected',
	'public',
	'return',
	'short',
	'static',
	'super',
	'switch',
	'synchronized',
	'this',
	'throw',
	'throws',
	'transient',
	'true',
	'try',
	'typeof',
	'var',
	'void',
	'while',
	'with',
	'yield'
])

name: mangleIdentifier
description: Convert a name to a valid JavaScript identifier.

name: needsMangle
description: `false` iff `name` is a valid JavaScript identifier.

name: propertyNameOk
description: `true` iff `name` can be used as a property name using dot syntax (`a.b`).

name: unmangle
description: Undoes {@link mangleIdentifier}.

name: forbiddenNames
description: Set of JavaScript keywords.

name: src/render.js
render
description: Creates JavaScript source code from a {@link Node}.

params.name: options.ugly
params.description: If true, will not output any whitespace.

name: renderWithSourceMap
description: Same as {@link render}, but with a source map as part of the output.

name: src/util.js
identifier
description: Mangles name and makes an {@link Identifier}.

name: loc
description: Assigns `loc` to `ast` and returns it.

name: member
description:
Creates a member expression for `propertyName` in `object`,
using dot syntax (`a.b`) if possible, and falling back to `a['b']`.

name: propertyIdOrLiteral
description:
An Identifier if propertyName is a valid JavaScript property name;
otherwise a Literal string.

name: toStatement
description:
Convert any {@link Node} into one that can be used as the content of a line.
(esast requires all expression lines to be wrapped with {@link ExpressionStatement}.)
